Hell, the only good commie is a dead commie, I say.  Hey, at basic training they told us the Veetcong were the &quot;Breakfast of Champions.&quot;  Them commies were a sneaky and insidious bunch and deserved no mercy.  <br><br>
America for me, right or wrong.  We were sold down the river by all those nabobs of negativism, including the Washington Post.  General Westmoreland knew how to fight the right kind of war and he told eveyone so, he even saw &quot;Light at the end of the Tunnel.&quot;  We were sold out by the pinkos, plain and simple.  All of us who were in country, knew that we could win with only a little more time, money and men.  We all know, that everyday we were in Vietnam the war was going our way and that victory was near.  <br><br>
Our leaders, who had a great deal of inside info (not accessible to the rest of us), had the Veetnom War well in hand, until we were all betrayed by leftists and protestors. Americans know how to fight, just look at how Sherman and Sheridan took care of the Redman problem.  Hey, do you thing they were commies too?<br><br>
We should have nuked em.  <br><br>

